{{Orphan|date=January 2012}}

'''Tukumana Te Taniwha''' (1862&ndash;1941) was a notable New Zealand tribal leader and historian of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent. He identified with the [[Ngāti Maru (Hauraki)|Ngāti Maru]] and [[Ngāti Whanaunga]] [[iwi]]. He was born in the [[Coromandel, New Zealand|Coromandel]], [[New Zealand]] in 1862. His mother, Karukino Te Taniwha, was the daughter of [[Te Horeta|Te Horeta Te Taniwha]].<ref name="DNZB Te Taniwha">{{DNZB|title=Tukumana Te Taniwha|first= Te Ahukaramu Charles|last= Royal|id=3t20|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

